modules.description: Provides infix operators for indexed access, modification, and transformation of vector-like structures, including safe and unsafe indexing, assignment, and mapping. Supports operations such as appending vectors, combining elements with cartesian products, and sequencing transformations using monadic-like combinators. Enables concise manipulation of data streams and ranges within a typed, immutable framework.

Provides operations for resizing, appending, and modifying elements in-place with fine-grained control over mutability. Works with dynamic arrays that automatically manage their capacity and ensure memory safety. Used to efficiently handle growing datasets in performance-critical applications, such as parsing large input streams or implementing data processing pipelines.

provides a set of infix operators for manipulating vectors with fine-grained mutability control, enabling safe and unsafe indexed access, modification, and transformation. It supports operations like appending, cartesian products, and monadic sequencing, working with vectors of type ('a, 'p) t. Examples include mapping over elements, assigning values at specific indices, and combining vectors into new structures. The module allows for expressive, type-safe data processing within read-only or read-write contexts.
